## 3. Artistic style and expectations

The Client acknowledges that:

1. they have reviewed the Artist’s portfolio, website, social media and/or example works before booking;
2. they are engaging the Artist because of the Artist’s distinctive watercolour style;
3. watercolour is expressive, interpretive and handmade, and the final artwork will not be a photographic or exact likeness;
4. colours, expressions, proportions, composition and details may be interpreted artistically;
5. live painting is affected by lighting, venue conditions, time available, subject positioning, weather, movement, access and event flow; and
6. subjective dissatisfaction with style, composition or artistic interpretation is not, by itself, a failure by the Artist to provide the services with due care and skill.

Nothing in this clause limits the Client’s rights under the Australian Consumer Law.

