2. to make the artwork photorealistic;
3. to alter subjective artistic choices;
4. to add details not visible or available at the event;
5. to incorporate new reference materials after the event;
6. to substantially alter composition;
7. to change likeness beyond reasonable finishing touches; or
8. to respond to requests generated by artificial intelligence tools.

